-- Benelux Stocks: OctoPlus, Montea Shares Are Active in Brussels, Amsterdam
-- Fred Pals
-- 2010-06-30T08:31:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/benelux-stocks-octoplus-montea-shares-are-active-in-brussels-amsterdam.html

          
          
             The  Amsterdam Exchanges Index  gained
0.63, or 0.2 percent, to 319.66 as of 10:28 a.m. local time,
trimming the decline this quarter to 7.1 percent. Belgium’s
 Bel20 Index  rose 7.68, or 0.3 percent, to 2,390.16.  
 The following are among the most active stocks in the
Benelux markets today. Symbols are in parentheses.  
 OctoPlus NV  (OCTO NA) rose the most in more than a year,
gaining 15 cents, or 14 percent, to 1.25 euros. The developer of
a hepatitis C treatment agreed to develop a controlled-release
formulation of an undisclosed compound for Novartis AG for an
undisclosed sum.  
 Montea SCA  (MONT BB) rose the most in more than a week,
adding 74 cents, or 3.5 percent, to 21.85 euros. Bank Degroof
upgraded its recommendation on the owner of warehouses in
Belgium and France to “accumulate” from “hold.”  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
